==Removing shunts== 
Though there have been many cases of patients reaching "shunt independence", there is no common accord in which doctors can agree in which a patient might survive without a shunt.  Another problem with shunt removal is that it is very difficult to discern when a patient might be shunt independent without very specific conditions.  Overall shunt removal is a rare but not unheard of procedure.<ref>Iannelli, A., Rea, G., Rocco, C. D.; CSF Shunt Removal in Children with Hydrocephalus; ''Acta Neurchir (Wien)''; 147:503-507 (2005)</ref> 

